introduction_en:
The IUFRO Regional Congress for Asia and Oceania 2016 aims at reaching a common understanding about the status and trends of forests and the consequent research needs towards sustainable forestry development under such changes. It also aims at generating research synergies for well-informed policy and decision making to meet the forest governance and management demands in the transition period.
Themes
1. Sustainable forest management for enhanced provision of ecosystem services;
2. Forest and landscape rehabilitation and restoration;
3. Combating desertification, disaster and risk management, and climate change mitigation and adaptation;
4. Planted forests for fostering a greener economy;
5. Innovative technologies for bio-energy, bio-materials and other products;
6. Urban forestry for human health and community well-being;
7. Social and cultural aspects of forests, including traditional knowledge, human health, community 
    participation and gender roles;
8. Forest and agro-forest management for food security, enhanced livelihoods and non-timber forest
    products.

In 1919, the Faculty of Physics and Mathematics of the Irkutsk State University was opened, and that had
marked the beginning of the 100-year history of the mathematical education and basic mathematical research
in the Eastern Siberia.
On November 1, 2019, the founder of the Irkutsk School of Optimal Control, the first director of the Institute
of Mathematics, Economics and Informatics of the Irkutsk State University, the Honored Scientist of the
Russian Federation – Professor Oleg Vladimirovich Vasiliev (1939-2002) – would have turned 80 years old.
This International Symposium is devoted to these two memorable dates, and we expect it to become an
international forum for discussion of a variety of fundamental mathematical problems within the framework
of the triad "dynamic systems – optimization – mathematical modelling of processes and phenomena".
A wide range of diverse issues are planned for discussion at the symposium:
 qualitative analysis of diverse equations describing dynamic processes (including differential,
integral, integro-differential, differential-algebraic, integro-algebraic, functional-differential,
operator, stochastic, and difference equations);
 inverse and ill-posed problems for equations and systems;
 analytical and numerical methods for solving equations and related issues;
 necessary and sufficient conditions for optimality, methods for solving optimization problems;
 new approaches and methods of decision-making under uncertainty and/or conflict;
 controllability and stability of dynamical systems with related issues;
 mathematical modelling of natural processes and phenomena;
 mathematical modelling for a wide range of technical, informational, economic, environmental,
biological, and medical problems.

introduction_mn:
About
The Society serves, represents, and speaks for scholars of the history of East Asian science, technology, and medicine worldwide. It was founded on 4 August 1990, on the occasion of the Sixth International Conference on the History of Science in China, held in Cambridge, UK. It also constitutes the East Asia Commission of the International Union for History and Philosophy of Science and Technology – Division of History of Science and Technology (IUHPST-DHST).
The Society’s activities consist of:
organizing a plenary conference every few years; the next conference (16th ICHSEA) will take place in 2023 at Goethe University Frankfurt, Germany;
seeking support for conferences and other activities from international organisations;
finding means to aid scholars to enter the field;
sponsoring publication of refereed research reports and monographs;
publishing a journal, East Asian Science, Technology and Medicine (currently edited by Catherine Jami, EHESS, Paris, France).

